>>> PROJECT - project description
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------


quick start -----------------------------------------------------------------

    1 - edit etc/venv/requirements.txt to contain the packages you required
    2 - run bin/venv-create to generate the .venv/ directory
    3 - run bin/venv-python to try it 
    4 - run bin/corporation.department.project.application.component to try it


discussion ------------------------------------------------------------------

There are many packages available for the management of python
environments -- too many to list here without doing a disservice any I
would have missed were I attempt to list them all.

The end result is the installation of a single virtual environment, and
packages installed therein.

bin/venv-create -- bash script to install venv
bin/pip-init -- bash script to install packages into .venv/





